  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "If you have lost your Chase debit card, it\u2019s important to act quickly to protect your account. Here are the steps you should follow:\n\n1. **Report the Loss or Theft:**\n   - Immediately call Chase Customer Service at 1-800-935-9935 to report your lost card. This service is available 24/7.\n\n2. **Lock Your Card (if applicable):**\n   - If you've set up online or mobile banking, you can temporarily lock your card to prevent unauthorized use. This can often be done through the Chase Mobile app or online banking site.\n\n3. **Monitor Your Account:**\n   - Check your account for any unauthorized transactions. Report any suspicious activity to Chase as soon as possible.\n\n4. **Request a Replacement Card:**\n   - Request a new card through the customer service representative, or order one through online banking or the Chase Mobile app. Typically, a replacement card is sent within 3-5 business days.\n\n5. **Update Automatic Payments:**\n   - Once you receive your new card, remember to update any automatic payments with your new card details.\n\n6. **Review Chase's Fraud Protection:**\n   - Familiarize yourself with Chase\u2019s Zero Liability Protection. This policy means you won\u2019t be held responsible for unauthorized transactions if you report them promptly.\n\nTaking these steps will help ensure your account remains secure and minimize the inconvenience of a lost card.",
